    <Overview>
        <Title>Choose the correct missing reasoning of an argument</Title>

        <!-- Here are the guidelines. Recommend keeping these short and crisp. -->
        <Text>There are several incomplete arguments to various topics with a gap.</Text>
        <Text>Your task is to choose the logically correct explanation of reasoning.</Text>
        <Text>If none of the two first option makes sense, select the third option.</Text>
        <Text>Some of them are tricky and need logical thinking.</Text>
    </Overview>

    <!--
1 Humans are naturally omnivorous, as dictated by our physiological needs, and veganism is a health risk. And since [explanation], I claim that Veganism is not good for everyone
0 vegans can figure out how to eat without being at risk
1 vegans can't figure out how to eat without being at risk
-->
